OL,3,CBreast cancer patients given 'more
OL,4,Cextensive than necessary' surgery,
OL,5,Csays trust
OL,7,FOver the last few months, patients who
OL,8,Fhave undergone surgery through the
OL,9,Fbreast service in 2024 have been
OL,10,Fcontacted.
OL,12,FAccording to the trust, 123 cases of
OL,13,Fcare have been reviewed, with more
OL,14,Fthan 80 patients taking part in
OL,15,Fdiscussions with the service about how
OL,16,Ftheir care could have been improved.
OL,18,FPatients whose care has been reviewed
OL,19,Fand was found to be appropriate are
OL,20,Falso being contacted.
